.TH GEN-LICENSE "1" "February 2026" "gen-license 202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gen-license \- Software license file generator with templates
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gen-license
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR] [\fI\,LICENSE_TYPE\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gen-license
is a license file generator that creates LICENSE.md files for software projects using customizable templates. It supports common open source licenses including MIT, GPL, BSD, Apache, and others, with automatic author and date substitution.
.PP
The script provides template management from local files or remote git repositories, variable substitution for author information, and support for custom license templates. Generated files are properly formatted with the current year and configured author information.
.PP
gen-license is designed for developers who need to quickly add appropriate licensing to their projects.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B gen-license [license_type]
Create a LICENSE.md file using the specified license template (default: wtfpl)
.TP
.B gen-license list
List all available license templates from default and custom directories
.TP
.B gen-license download
Download license templates from the configured git repository to local custom directory
.TP
.B gen-license custom [file]
Use a custom license file from local path or remote URL
